sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K606018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 poymerase autoamplifier for B. Subtilis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a T7 amplifier. The pT7 activate the production T7 polymerase in a positive amplification loop
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cyrille Pauthenier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Comes from the biobricks I712074 K143031 and K145001

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K606017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 polymerase expression casette for Bacillus Subtilis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Fused with the RBS SpoVG, this biobrick is the expression cassette for B. Subtilis of the T7 polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cyrille Pauthenier

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I712074
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 promoter (strong promoter from T7 bacteriophage)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 promoter is very specific promoter which is transcribed only by specific T7 RNA polymerase. Usually this promoter is used in expression systems where T7 promoter is cotransfected with T7 RNA polymerase. That ensures strong transcription of desired genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Rok Gaber

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RBS-spoVG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SpoVG ribosome binding site (RBS) for B. subtilis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Description: SpoVG is an endogenous ribosome binding site from B.subtilis. The sequence of the spoVG ribosome binding site is AAAGGUGGUGA which is complementary to the sequence UUUCCUCCACU from the 3' region of the 16s rRNA from B.subtilis. Previous research showed that the predicted binding energy of the 16s rRNA to the RBS is -19kcal <cite>1</cite>
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: James Chappell
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was taken from a previous research paper [1] and was constructed by Geneart.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to ensure that the RBS is functional the actual ribosome binding site was maintained and the distance between the RBS and the start codon maintained. In order to conform to the biobrick standard the sequence flanking the RBS had to be changed but the distance between the promoter and RBS, and start codon and RBS was maintained.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T7pol
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 RNA polymerase with LVA tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Demeulemeester and Benjamien Moeyaert
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Fuse the LVA tag to the T7 coding region
